  "body": "A current full-synced node looks like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\n+-----------------+--------------------+------------+\r\n|    DATABASE     |      CATEGORY      |    SIZE    |\r\n+-----------------+--------------------+------------+\r\n| Key-Value store | Headers            | 49.10 MiB  |\r\n| Key-Value store | Bodies             | 1.84 GiB   |\r\n| Key-Value store | Receipts           | 3.72 GiB   |\r\n| Key-Value store | Difficulties       | 8.60 MiB   |\r\n| Key-Value store | Block number->hash | 7.63 MiB   |\r\n| Key-Value store | Block hash->number | 350.68 MiB |\r\n| Key-Value store | Transaction index  | 19.66 GiB  |\r\n| Key-Value store | Bloombit index     | 1.20 GiB   |\r\n| Key-Value store | Trie nodes         | 246.71 GiB |\r\n| Key-Value store | Trie preimages     | 19.17 GiB  |\r\n| Key-Value store | Clique snapshots   | 0.00 B     |\r\n| Key-Value store | Singleton metadata | 139.00 B   |\r\n| Ancient store   | Headers            | 3.63 GiB   |\r\n| Ancient store   | Bodies             | 69.73 GiB  |\r\n| Ancient store   | Receipts           | 29.50 GiB  |\r\n| Ancient store   | Difficulties       | 136.95 MiB |\r\n| Ancient store   | Block number->hash | 321.76 MiB |\r\n| Light client    | CHT trie nodes     | 0.00 B     |\r\n| Light client    | Bloom trie nodes   | 0.00 B     |\r\n+-----------------+--------------------+------------+\r\n|                         TOTAL        | 396.00 GIB |\r\n+-----------------+--------------------+------------+\r\n```\r\n\r\nPart of this is 20GB wasted for the pre-images. One option is to completely disable recording pre-images. Another is to introduce an in-memory GC for them similar to the trie GC (simpler as there are no ref graphs, just a single counter).\r\n\r\nPosting this as an issue so the idea doesn't get lost.",
